CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 15, reads: "NAACP Membership - Members of the Alpha Wives made their initial payment towards a life membership in NAACP recently when the group met at the home of Mrs. Nathan Page. Mrs. Eric Springer, president of the Alpha Wives, presented the check for $100 to Herbert Wilkinson, executive secretary of the Pittsburgh NAACP, as Mrs. Henry D. McCullough, Mrs. LeBertha [Lee Bertha] Nicklos and Mrs. Howard Hairston look on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cecile Springer presenting check for NAACP membership to Herbert Wilkinson on behalf of the Alpha Wives, surrounded by Mrs. Henry D. McCullough, Lee Bertha Nicklos, and Mrs. Howard Hairston, posed in home of Nathan Page
